  "prompt": "Does cctv works during power cut?",
  "response": "Traditional CCTV (closed-circuit television) systems that rely on mains power will **not work during a power cut** because they depend on electricity to operate. However, there are ways to ensure your CCTV system continues functioning during a power outage:\n\n1. **Battery Backup (UPS - Uninterruptible Power Supply)**:\n   - A UPS can provide temporary power to your CCTV system and its associated equipment (like the DVR/NVR) during a power cut. The duration depends on the battery capacity and the power consumption of the system.\n\n2. **PoE (Power over Ethernet) with Backup**:\n   - If your CCTV cameras use PoE (powered through Ethernet cables), you can connect the PoE switch or injector to a UPS to keep the cameras operational during a power outage.\n\n3. **Solar-Powered Cameras**:\n   - Some CCTV cameras are solar-powered and can continue operating during a power cut, as long as they have sufficient charge.\n\n4. **Cameras with Built-in Batteries**:\n   - Certain wireless CCTV cameras come with built-in rechargeable batteries, allowing them to function for a limited time without mains power.\n\n5. **Mobile Network Backup**:\n   - Some advanced systems use 4G/5G connectivity as a backup during power cuts, ensuring that the cameras remain connected and functional.\n\n6. **Generator Backup**:\n   - For longer power outages, a generator can power your entire CCTV system and other essential devices.\n\nAlways ensure that your recording device (DVR/NVR) and network equipment (if applicable) are also supported by a backup power source to maintain uninterrupted surveillance.",
